references.paper_title: Entropy Coding of Unordered Data Structures
references.reason: This paper introduces the core concept of shuffle coding, which is the foundation of the methods presented in the current work.
This paper presents an autoregressive shuffle coding method for multisets that the current work generalizes to arbitrary unordered objects.

references.paper_title: Random Edge Coding: One-Shot Bits-Back Coding of Large Labeled Graphs
references.reason: This paper introduces the Pólya urn model for graphs, which is used in the current work to improve compression rates.
This paper introduces asymmetric numeral systems (ANS), which is used as the underlying entropy coding method in the current work.
This paper introduces the nauty and Traces software, which is used in the current work to compute automorphism groups and color refinement for graphs.
